# LldpSender configuration
#
# Each line defines a physical adapter to send LLDP on:
#   AdapterGUID,MACAddress,PortName
#
# AdapterGUID: The Windows network adapter GUID (from Get-NetAdapter -Physical)
# MACAddress:  The adapter's MAC address (with or without separators)
# PortName:    Human-readable name sent in the LLDP Port ID TLV
#
# If this file is absent, the service auto-discovers physical Ethernet adapters.
#
# Find your adapter GUIDs and MACs with:
#   Get-NetAdapter -Physical | Select-Object Name, InterfaceGuid, MacAddress

# Example:
# {7F2D754B-6031-4989-9698-7C5169055D41},0C-C4-7A-CF-AE-9E,Ethernet
# {74847FBD-103C-4F34-A4E1-F7F2C84FEB20},0C-C4-7A-CF-AE-9F,Ethernet 2
